\cs15\fs16\insrsid5911984 \chatn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5911984 Vanishing Indians}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15670295 {\*\atrfstart 415666249}
Not one of the Indians within a circumference of many miles, could be found, who could understand her. So that she could communicate only by signs.
\par 
\par It appears from her narative, that after leaving the vessel in search of her child, she wandered about for several hours, and when she found it, the wild dogs which infest the island, even to the present day, had killed, and nearly devoured it. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid7633252 {\*\atrfend 415666249}{\*\atnid SS}{\*\atnauthor Sara Schwebel}\chatn {\*\annotation{\*\atnref 415666249}{\*\atndate -1490490042}\ltrpar \pard\plain \ltrpar
\s16\ql \li0\ri0\sa160\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs15\fs16\insrsid7633252 \chatn }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7633252 Signs easily interpreted}}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15670295 We can better imagine the feelin
gs of a mother at such a time, than describe them. When she returned to the spot where she had left the vessel, to tell of her sorrows, for the loss of her child, that too was gone, and was bearing away her kindred and friends from her sight.
\par 
\par Could she ha
ve realized, then, that for eighteen long years she must live <i>alone</i> in the world, without one kind word of comfort, one cheering look from a friendly eye, or one smile of recognition, it would have been too much for even her wild, but womanly natur
e to bear, and with her, as with us, it is well that we know not the future.
\par 
\par From day to day, she lived in hope, beguiling the weary hours in providing for her wants. With snares made of her hair she caught birds ; and with the skins, properly prepared, sh
e made her clothing ; her needles were neatly made of bone, and cactus thorns ; her thread was of sinews from the seal : in these, and many other articles found in her possession, she exhibited much of the native ingenuity she possessed.
\par 
\par Whether she still remembered her own language or not, will forever remain a myatery. {\*\atrfstart 415666250}
She was very gentle, and kind, especially to children, and nothing seemed to please her more than to be near them : and the poor woman would often shed tears, while attempting to describe,
 by signs, her own little one which had been killed and eaten by the wild dogs.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs15\fs16\insrsid8933019 {\*\atrfend 415666250}{\*\atnid SS}{\*\atnauthor Sara Schwebel}\chatn {\*\annotation{\*\atnref 415666250}
